1
00:00:01,502 --> 00:00:03,695
The seminar ends today, huh?

2
00:00:03,695 --> 00:00:05,439
It's the last time.

3
00:00:05,439 --> 00:00:09,309
I'm glad I met you, Seita-san.

4
00:00:09,309 --> 00:00:11,177
Likewise.

5
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:24,910
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by
Sustainable Heartbeats Team @Viki.com </i>

6
00:00:34,825 --> 00:00:35,855
Seita-san?

7
00:00:35,855 --> 00:00:41,372
Sorry, I suddenly... A goodbye hug. For the last time.

8
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:47,815
Nijiro is attending English lessons, so I got influenced by him.

9
00:00:47,815 --> 00:00:53,085
Oh, Hayate came back from overseas, so he sometimes does this too.

10
00:00:53,085 --> 00:00:54,855
Is that so?

11
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:57,205
I'll get going, then.

12
00:00:57,205 --> 00:00:59,259
Sure. See you next timeー

13
00:00:59,259 --> 00:01:03,999
I wish you success... in going independent.

14
00:01:15,365 --> 00:01:18,285
Huh? Independent? Who?

15
00:01:18,285 --> 00:01:19,795
Me.

16
00:01:19,795 --> 00:01:21,305
I don't get what you're talking about.

17
00:01:21,305 --> 00:01:23,817
Did I not tell you before, Dad?

18
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:28,088
I didn't hear about that. Do you even have money to go independent?

19
00:01:28,088 --> 00:01:29,857
I've saved up enough.

20
00:01:29,857 --> 00:01:33,292
The reason why I came back to live here is also to save enough capital for my startup.

21
00:01:33,292 --> 00:01:34,995
So it wasn't for my sake?

22
00:01:34,995 --> 00:01:37,535
Well, partly that, too.

23
00:01:37,535 --> 00:01:39,208
Did you tell Hayate about it?

24
00:01:39,208 --> 00:01:41,168
- Why should I?
- After all, the two of you areー

25
00:01:41,168 --> 00:01:44,237
I'll lend my hand in anything if it's for Kyoka's dream.

26
00:01:44,237 --> 00:01:46,907
- Welcome home, Hayate.
- I'm back.

27
00:01:46,907 --> 00:01:51,095
For now, shall I check with my friends about any rent-free venues where you can conduct lessons?

28
00:01:51,095 --> 00:01:53,038
Really? Thanks!

29
00:01:53,038 --> 00:01:54,648
Hayate, you're okay with that?

30
00:01:54,648 --> 00:01:56,049
Dad...

31
00:01:56,049 --> 00:02:00,197
You've gotten it wrong all this time. We're not in that kind of relationship. Totally not.

32
00:02:00,197 --> 00:02:01,765
- W-What?
- "What?"

33
00:02:01,765 --> 00:02:03,955
Unfortunately, not yet.

34
00:02:03,955 --> 00:02:07,665
Jeez, if you say it like that, my dad will really take you seriously.

35
00:02:07,665 --> 00:02:11,412
Huh? In that case, that someone you like is...

36
00:02:12,825 --> 00:02:16,115
Anyway, rather than who I like or dislike,

37
00:02:16,115 --> 00:02:17,805
there's something more important.

38
00:02:17,805 --> 00:02:21,315
Right now, I'm only focused on going independent, and I'm going all the way.

39
00:02:25,023 --> 00:02:29,149
From now on, I'll work hard to live up to your expectations.

40
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,950
Good night.

41
00:02:33,995 --> 00:02:37,790
What exactly is Kyoka's happiness?

42
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:41,525
What would you say if it were you, Yoko-san?

43
00:02:42,205 --> 00:02:43,975
Yoko-san?

44
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:46,665
Yoko-san!

45
00:02:47,455 --> 00:02:50,465
<i>Things that are important to me.</i>

46
00:02:53,974 --> 00:02:55,445
<i>[Yoga | Independence | My own studio]</i>

47
00:02:55,445 --> 00:02:56,995
<i>[Funding | Time | Attracting customers]</i>

48
00:02:56,995 --> 00:02:59,138
<i>[Friends | Freedom from Dad]</i>

49
00:02:59,138 --> 00:03:01,808
<i>[Seita-san]</i>

50
00:03:09,156 --> 00:03:11,565
<i>[Things that are important to me]</i>

51
00:03:11,565 --> 00:03:14,178
<i>[Nijiro | Money | Health]</i>

52
00:03:14,178 --> 00:03:15,910
<i>[Me time | Curry]</i>

53
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,890
<i>[Kyoka-san]</i>

54
00:03:25,155 --> 00:03:27,925
I guess we'll never meet again.

55
00:03:38,779 --> 00:03:47,671
<i>[Is Love Sustainable? - Episode 5]</i>

56
00:03:48,875 --> 00:03:51,031
<i>"Real fulfilment".</i>

57
00:03:51,031 --> 00:03:55,211
<i>"Unlike deriving fulfillment from the internet,</i>

58
00:03:55,211 --> 00:04:01,065
<i>it's the fulfillment one derives in real life".</i>

59
00:04:08,148 --> 00:04:10,638
<i>What do you think? Pretty, right?</i>

60
00:04:10,638 --> 00:04:12,358
<i>Flowers?</i>

61
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:14,505
<i>That's right. Flowers.</i>

62
00:04:14,505 --> 00:04:19,125
<i>They're flowers, but more specifically, gladiolus.</i>

63
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:21,425
<i>Gladiolus?</i>

64
00:04:21,425 --> 00:04:23,475
<i>So these are gladiolus?</i>

65
00:04:23,475 --> 00:04:25,202
<i>Yes.</i>

66
00:04:28,569 --> 00:04:30,209
<i>They give a kind smell.</i>

67
00:04:30,209 --> 00:04:31,759
<i>Yup.</i>

68
00:04:43,162 --> 00:04:45,045
Good morning.

69
00:04:45,045 --> 00:04:46,825
Oh, good morning.

70
00:04:46,825 --> 00:04:48,221
What are you doing?

71
00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:50,825
Oh, these are gladiolus.

72
00:04:50,825 --> 00:04:52,968
- I see that you like flowers.
- Not really.

73
00:04:52,968 --> 00:04:54,494
But just now...

74
00:04:54,494 --> 00:04:56,505
My wife taught me that.

75
00:04:56,505 --> 00:04:59,165
- Your wife?
- That's right.

76
00:05:00,245 --> 00:05:08,808
Initially, my knowledge of flowers was only limited to knowing whether they are white, red, big, or small.

77
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:12,455
But one day, I saw the flowers that my wife decorated our home with,

78
00:05:12,455 --> 00:05:16,535
and for the first time, realized that our feelings can be healed by flowers.

79
00:05:16,535 --> 00:05:18,852
From then on, I started knowing more flower terminologies.

80
00:05:18,852 --> 00:05:21,025
It's wonderful to hear that.

81
00:05:21,025 --> 00:05:24,575
What was your wife like?

82
00:05:26,555 --> 00:05:27,975
Oh, I'm sorry for being rude.

83
00:05:27,975 --> 00:05:31,631
Don't be. I just wasn't sure how to explain it.

84
00:05:31,631 --> 00:05:35,275
She was sort of a unique person to me.

85
00:05:35,275 --> 00:05:40,265
She was the one who taught me the real meaning of words.

86
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:43,905
If you write down the word "the sky above",

87
00:05:43,905 --> 00:05:46,835
it has another meaning, which is "to be in another world".

88
00:05:46,835 --> 00:05:49,865
When you think about how it's interpreted...

89
00:05:53,334 --> 00:05:54,388
<i>No!</i>

90
00:05:54,388 --> 00:05:56,515
<i>It'll be all right,</i>

91
00:05:56,515 --> 00:05:58,855
<i>- Rintaro!
- No, no no!</i>

92
00:05:58,855 --> 00:06:02,675
<i>I can't do it! Yoko-san! Yoko-san!</i>

93
00:06:02,675 --> 00:06:05,525
<i>But don't you want to know</i>

94
00:06:05,525 --> 00:06:07,567
<i>how it's like to be in another world?</i>

95
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,536
<i>- Please do it.
- Okay.</i>

96
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:12,285
<i>I can't! I can't! No, no, no, no!</i>

97
00:06:12,285 --> 00:06:15,365
<i>- You'll be fine! Come on!
- I can't do it! No!</i>

98
00:06:15,365 --> 00:06:21,720
Instead of being in another world, I fainted and ended up having a bad experience.

99
00:06:23,038 --> 00:06:25,635
Just like that, she brought me to all kinds of places.

100
00:06:25,635 --> 00:06:29,305
In reality, half of them were by force.

101
00:06:29,305 --> 00:06:33,445
She showed me a real world that cannot be found in books.

102
00:06:35,329 --> 00:06:38,298
She was really a wonderful wife.

103
00:06:38,298 --> 00:06:41,845
But I have to move on.

104
00:06:41,845 --> 00:06:46,583
My wife wrote me a letter before she passed away, asking me to remarry.

105
00:06:50,135 --> 00:06:54,700
I'll cheer you on in your marriage hunting, Sawada-san.

106
00:06:55,645 --> 00:06:58,315
Let's work hard at it together.

107
00:06:58,315 --> 00:07:00,195
Sure.

108
00:07:03,724 --> 00:07:05,715
Oh, swing your arms like this.

109
00:07:05,715 --> 00:07:08,025
- Swing it widely.
- That's right.

110
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:16,715
Dad, where have you been?

111
00:07:16,715 --> 00:07:20,145
- I went for a walk.
- This early in the morning?

112
00:07:20,145 --> 00:07:21,845
You went alone, wearing this?

113
00:07:21,845 --> 00:07:24,189
Doesn't matter who I'm walking with, right?

114
00:07:24,189 --> 00:07:26,315
Who were you with?

115
00:07:26,315 --> 00:07:28,055
Ah, could it be a walking marriage hunt?

116
00:07:28,055 --> 00:07:32,345
No, it's not! It's the doctor, you know, my back pain.

117
00:07:32,345 --> 00:07:35,285
It's the doctor at your friend's clinic.

118
00:07:35,285 --> 00:07:39,155
She suggested that I walk often to prevent my back pain from acting up.

119
00:07:39,155 --> 00:07:44,375
I heard that the doctor at Suzu's clinic is a very beautiful woman.

120
00:07:44,375 --> 00:07:47,765
Different people have d-different standards of beauty.

121
00:07:47,765 --> 00:07:49,538
- So how was it?
- I'm taking a shower.

122
00:07:49,538 --> 00:07:52,674
- Door closing.
- How was it? Was it that doctor?

123
00:07:52,674 --> 00:07:55,105
- I'm really curious.
- Yeah.

124
00:07:55,105 --> 00:07:57,564
Firmly, on the soles of your feet,

125
00:07:57,564 --> 00:08:00,541
and tuck in your tummy.

126
00:08:00,541 --> 00:08:02,165
Can you breathe?

127
00:08:02,165 --> 00:08:06,655
I'm sorry. Regarding your offer to let me manage the studios,

128
00:08:06,655 --> 00:08:09,235
I'm afraid I'll have to turn it down.

129
00:08:09,235 --> 00:08:12,505
Is that so? What a shame.

130
00:08:12,505 --> 00:08:16,555
Since you're not interested in managing them, it won't work out even if I force you to.

131
00:08:16,555 --> 00:08:21,570
I feel honored to be considered for the role. I'm sorry.

132
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:24,915
In that case,

133
00:08:25,905 --> 00:08:29,785
can I entrust you with this event, then?

134
00:08:29,785 --> 00:08:33,175
Oh, we're doing it again this year, right?
<i>[Tamagawa Sustainable Festival - Live in the moment]</i>

135
00:08:33,175 --> 00:08:36,825
Sure. I'll work hard to make it a success.

136
00:08:36,825 --> 00:08:38,945
I'm counting on you.

137
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:54,510
<i>[Hinata Orthopedic Clinic]</i>

138
00:08:55,505 --> 00:08:57,205
Hello.

139
00:08:57,205 --> 00:08:59,455
Oh, Kyoka-san! What brings you here today?

140
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:01,915
I was nearby, so I thought we could have lunch together.

141
00:09:01,915 --> 00:09:03,855
Oh, sounds good!

142
00:09:03,855 --> 00:09:07,355
The patient in consultation right now is the last one. You can sit there for a while.

143
00:09:07,355 --> 00:09:09,745
- Thank you very much.
- Okay.

144
00:09:09,745 --> 00:09:11,345
Nakayama-san...

145
00:09:11,345 --> 00:09:15,505
- You forgot your coat.
- Sorry, and thank you.

146
00:09:15,505 --> 00:09:18,095
- Please take care.
- Huh?

147
00:09:22,315 --> 00:09:24,165
Wait...

148
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:31,671
I didn't know you're a doctor at Suzu's clinic.

149
00:09:31,671 --> 00:09:34,505
Thank you for taking care of my dad.

150
00:09:34,505 --> 00:09:37,935
Is the walking exercise with my dad also for his back pain?

151
00:09:37,935 --> 00:09:41,525
Well, that's part of the reason,

152
00:09:41,525 --> 00:09:45,575
but he's also someone with whom I can discuss my marriage hunting.

153
00:09:45,575 --> 00:09:48,295
Wait, with my dad?

154
00:09:48,295 --> 00:09:53,068
Yes. He knows a lot about marriage and husband-wife relationships.

155
00:09:53,068 --> 00:09:54,494
My dad does?

156
00:09:54,494 --> 00:10:00,835
The other day, too. He chatted with me a lot about his late wife.

157
00:10:01,435 --> 00:10:03,825
Your mom was a wonderful woman.

158
00:10:04,655 --> 00:10:08,675
So he's now able to open up and talk about my mom?

159
00:10:11,344 --> 00:10:14,247
When my mom passed away,

160
00:10:16,355 --> 00:10:19,715
<i>it looked like a part of him has died.</i>

161
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:27,633
I really had a hard time back then.

162
00:10:27,633 --> 00:10:33,165
Well, in the first place, my dad wasn't good at living on his own.

163
00:10:33,165 --> 00:10:37,904
Is that so? He looked like he enjoyed himself when we chatted that day.

164
00:10:37,904 --> 00:10:42,405
But since he's started marriage hunting, that means he's all right now, no?

165
00:10:42,405 --> 00:10:45,655
I hope he'll marry someone soon,

166
00:10:45,655 --> 00:10:48,645
so that I can also devote everything to my work.

167
00:10:48,645 --> 00:10:53,710
Kyoka-san is planning to go independent, unlike a paid worker like me.

168
00:10:54,535 --> 00:10:59,635
Say, Hinata-san, when did you open your own clinic?

169
00:10:59,635 --> 00:11:03,315
I opened my own clinic when I was 37.

170
00:11:03,315 --> 00:11:05,875
I was working at a university hospital until I was in my 30s.

171
00:11:05,875 --> 00:11:08,461
Then why did you go independent?

172
00:11:09,405 --> 00:11:12,495
I didn't want to be a grumpy old lady in the future.

173
00:11:12,495 --> 00:11:14,065
Grumpy?

174
00:11:14,065 --> 00:11:18,485
When I become an old lady, I didn't want to complain that, "I should have started my own business".

175
00:11:18,485 --> 00:11:21,191
I'd much rather complain that I went independent,

176
00:11:21,191 --> 00:11:22,965
but it didn't work out.

177
00:11:22,965 --> 00:11:26,465
I thought old ladies would normally complain.

178
00:11:26,465 --> 00:11:30,625
Of course, people who don't complain are wonderful, myself included.

179
00:11:30,625 --> 00:11:35,715
But on the contrary, isn't it harder to trust people who just live normal lives

180
00:11:35,715 --> 00:11:38,500
without complaints or regrets?

181
00:11:39,195 --> 00:11:42,245
I'd rather complain that live regretting it.

182
00:11:42,245 --> 00:11:46,595
Then, by choosing work over marriage,

183
00:11:46,595 --> 00:11:48,141
when you're an old lady, you alsoー

184
00:11:48,141 --> 00:11:50,701
I didn't choose it.

185
00:11:50,701 --> 00:11:53,890
That was just how it happened.

186
00:11:54,675 --> 00:11:57,125
Now I feel like complaining.

187
00:11:58,085 --> 00:12:02,795
Perhaps you can tell me more specifically about your requirements in a female partner.

188
00:12:02,795 --> 00:12:05,615
My requirements in a female partner?

189
00:12:05,615 --> 00:12:11,175
That way, we can visualize the kind of future married life that you hope to have.

190
00:12:11,175 --> 00:12:14,965
It can be the food she likes, her hobbies, or anything will do.

191
00:12:21,102 --> 00:12:23,072
<i>Thank you.</i>

192
00:12:36,465 --> 00:12:40,115
Someone who can outlive me.

193
00:12:42,545 --> 00:12:45,185
I'm tired of sending people off.

194
00:12:46,805 --> 00:12:51,095
Wait, it's bad to make a lady feel that way, right?

195
00:12:52,515 --> 00:12:56,065
- Sawada-san, if you still have lingering feelings for your wife-
- No.

196
00:12:56,065 --> 00:12:59,485
I'm looking for a partner because I don't want to be a burden to my daughter.

197
00:13:01,395 --> 00:13:05,745
To be honest, I actually wanted Kyoka to get married.

198
00:13:05,745 --> 00:13:09,155
To just live a normal, happy life.

199
00:13:09,155 --> 00:13:11,025
A normal...

200
00:13:11,025 --> 00:13:15,480
Yes. A normal life, for my daughter.

201
00:13:16,225 --> 00:13:20,595
If I tell her that, she'll be mad at me for sure.

202
00:13:36,575 --> 00:13:38,465
<i>[Miscellaneous Items]</i>

203
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:06,655
That's right. Office yoga.
<i>[WisKids - Play Fun. Enjoy English]</i>

204
00:14:06,655 --> 00:14:08,985
You can consider it for your company. It's the rave now.

205
00:14:08,985 --> 00:14:11,835
Sounds like a good idea. Let me speak to my bosses.

206
00:14:11,835 --> 00:14:14,495
Thank you. She's a very good instructor.

207
00:14:14,495 --> 00:14:17,224
- Is that so?
- Mama!

208
00:14:17,224 --> 00:14:20,195
- Thanks for waiting.
- See you, Kana-chan.

209
00:14:20,195 --> 00:14:23,025
See you soon, Niji-kun.

210
00:14:23,025 --> 00:14:25,490
I miss you.

211
00:14:26,075 --> 00:14:28,525
- Bye bye.
- Bye bye.

212
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:32,165
- See you.
- See you.

213
00:14:32,895 --> 00:14:34,965
Hello.

214
00:14:34,965 --> 00:14:37,995
- Good evening. Nijiro, let's pack up.
- Hello.

215
00:14:37,995 --> 00:14:39,975
Hello.

216
00:14:40,625 --> 00:14:43,215
- Hello there.
- Hello.

217
00:14:48,245 --> 00:14:51,755
What were you planning to do the other day?

218
00:14:58,635 --> 00:15:00,925
I'm sorry, well...

219
00:15:01,385 --> 00:15:03,465
You're apologizing?

220
00:15:04,395 --> 00:15:08,745
If that's all you're prepared to do, then please stop doing that kind of thing.

221
00:15:13,475 --> 00:15:15,174
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

222
00:15:15,174 --> 00:15:16,665
Okay.

223
00:15:20,615 --> 00:15:25,015
"Tamagawa Sustainable Festival"?

224
00:15:25,015 --> 00:15:27,560
We'll conduct free public yoga sessions outdoors,

225
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:31,745
open our studios to the public, and set up a bazaar.

226
00:15:31,745 --> 00:15:33,605
It'll be a lot of work.

227
00:15:33,605 --> 00:15:36,765
Really? Live in the moment.

228
00:15:36,765 --> 00:15:41,005
It means "enjoy the present". That's the spirit of yoga.

229
00:15:41,005 --> 00:15:44,590
Oh, maybe I should invite Hinata-san too.

230
00:15:45,485 --> 00:15:48,011
H-Hinata-san?

231
00:15:48,011 --> 00:15:49,355
- Yup.
- Why?

232
00:15:49,355 --> 00:15:53,565
I was wondering who your walking date is,

233
00:15:53,565 --> 00:15:55,185
so I went to Suzu's clinic.

234
00:15:55,185 --> 00:15:58,165
- She's not my date.
- She's not, right?

235
00:15:58,165 --> 00:16:03,060
A wonderful woman like her wouldn't see you as a potential partner, right?

236
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:04,298
Do you remember?

237
00:16:04,298 --> 00:16:07,968
That doctor at the marriage meeting party.

238
00:16:07,968 --> 00:16:11,295
Oh, that beautiful lady?

239
00:16:11,295 --> 00:16:13,035
Sounds like fun to walk with her.

240
00:16:13,035 --> 00:16:15,325
I said it's not what you think.

241
00:16:15,325 --> 00:16:18,685
I'm going for a marriage meeting with someone else this time.

242
00:16:18,685 --> 00:16:20,625
Huh? Who is she?

243
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:22,215
I don't know the details,

244
00:16:22,215 --> 00:16:26,815
but it should be a nice person since Higashimura-san is doing the recommendation.

245
00:16:26,815 --> 00:16:30,200
