309
00:20:48,502 --> 00:20:50,482
<i>Positive, positive.</i>

310
00:20:50,482 --> 00:20:54,490
Positive and sustainable.

311
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:56,590
Positivable.

312
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:59,470
Positivable, positivable.

313
00:20:59,470 --> 00:21:02,122
- Looks like they're selling quite well.
- Yup.

314
00:21:02,122 --> 00:21:05,042
- Then please replenish them.
- Sure.

315
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:10,072
Excuse me, how much is this?

316
00:21:10,072 --> 00:21:12,342
All these cost 300 yen.

317
00:21:12,342 --> 00:21:14,274
Wow, that's cheap!

318
00:21:14,274 --> 00:21:17,284
<i>Reasonable!</i>

319
00:21:17,284 --> 00:21:19,132
Kyoka-san.

320
00:21:19,132 --> 00:21:21,782
Hinata-san, you really came!

321
00:21:21,782 --> 00:21:24,242
I wanted to try out your lesson.

322
00:21:24,242 --> 00:21:26,112
Thank you for your support.

323
00:21:26,112 --> 00:21:29,432
It'll start in around 30 minutes.

324
00:21:29,432 --> 00:21:31,722
Kyoka Sensei, it's time for you to prepare.

325
00:21:31,722 --> 00:21:34,402
- I'll take over from here.
- Thanks.

326
00:21:34,402 --> 00:21:37,362
- Well then, see you later.
- See you.

327
00:21:37,362 --> 00:21:40,552
- Please feel free to browse.
- Thank you.

328
00:21:40,552 --> 00:21:43,222
Hm. It's good. Feels like it's sustainable.

329
00:21:43,222 --> 00:21:45,232
You think so? It's sustainable?

330
00:21:45,232 --> 00:21:48,194
Yes, very.

331
00:21:48,194 --> 00:21:51,082
- Excuse me!
- Yes?

332
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:54,232
I'll get this one.

333
00:21:54,232 --> 00:21:55,290
Huh?

334
00:21:55,290 --> 00:21:58,810
<i>[And - Marriage Support Agent]</i>

335
00:22:00,910 --> 00:22:04,172
Hello. Your partner for today is here.

336
00:22:04,172 --> 00:22:06,152
Sure.

337
00:22:06,152 --> 00:22:10,582
Did you manage to go cherry blossom-viewing this year?

338
00:22:10,582 --> 00:22:11,498
Cherry blossom-viewing?

339
00:22:11,498 --> 00:22:15,869
- That's right, cherry blossom-viewing.
- Yes, I did.

340
00:22:15,869 --> 00:22:24,270
♫ <i>We start from here, dress for the breeze, it's time to live</i> ♫

341
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:28,502
Raise both arms from the sides, and interlock your fingers.

342
00:22:28,502 --> 00:22:31,472
Extend both index fingers upwards.

343
00:22:31,472 --> 00:22:34,872
Take a deep breath in,

344
00:22:34,872 --> 00:22:38,172
exhale, and lean to your right.

345
00:22:38,172 --> 00:22:42,162
Feel the stretch from your armpit down to your left side.

346
00:22:42,162 --> 00:22:45,482
Look up into the sky, and take another breath.

347
00:22:45,482 --> 00:22:47,902
Stretch your right leg back to rest on your toes,

348
00:22:47,902 --> 00:22:50,042
and turn your heel inwards.

349
00:22:50,042 --> 00:22:53,952
Turn your left leg outwards 90 degrees, and face forward.

350
00:22:53,952 --> 00:22:59,772
Extend your right arm through the sky, until it touches your ear.

351
00:22:59,772 --> 00:23:01,902
Raise the corners of your mouth slightly,

352
00:23:01,902 --> 00:23:05,302
and relax the muscles on your face.

353
00:23:05,302 --> 00:23:09,502
This is called the Savasana pose.

354
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:12,272
Entrust your body to the land,

355
00:23:12,272 --> 00:23:15,592
and clear your mind.

356
00:23:15,592 --> 00:23:17,822
You may be constantly busy

357
00:23:17,822 --> 00:23:21,482
with work or house chores.

358
00:23:22,570 --> 00:23:25,432
When you take time to stop thinking about them,

359
00:23:25,432 --> 00:23:29,008
it opens you to the deepest part of your emotions.

360
00:23:29,008 --> 00:23:32,652
Negative emotions like sadness, frustration,

361
00:23:32,652 --> 00:23:37,162
and things you complain about may start to emerge,

362
00:23:37,162 --> 00:23:39,732
but that's all part of you.

363
00:23:39,732 --> 00:23:42,682
Don't close off these painful feelings.

364
00:23:42,682 --> 00:23:44,802
Just merely feel them,

365
00:23:44,802 --> 00:23:46,962
let them out,

366
00:23:46,962 --> 00:23:49,432
and accept them.

367
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:53,422
Right now, sit upright,

368
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:58,762
and press your hands together in front of your chest.

369
00:23:58,762 --> 00:24:00,306
Thank you for the session.

370
00:24:00,306 --> 00:24:02,852
Thank you very much.

371
00:24:02,852 --> 00:24:07,452
Let's also give our thanks to those around us who have spent this time together with us.

372
00:24:07,452 --> 00:24:09,075
Thank you very much.

373
00:24:09,075 --> 00:24:14,185
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you very much.

374
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:16,352
Thank you.

375
00:24:16,352 --> 00:24:19,142
Thank you for the session.

376
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:22,592
- Thank you so much.
- How was it?

377
00:24:22,592 --> 00:24:26,102
My body is still quite inflexible, but your words really soothe me.

378
00:24:26,102 --> 00:24:29,932
But even now, I still can't apply whatever I said on myself.

379
00:24:29,932 --> 00:24:32,162
That's rather common for instructors.

380
00:24:32,162 --> 00:24:36,062
Orthopedic surgeons have stiff shoulders too, so we're no different.

381
00:24:37,630 --> 00:24:38,822
Kyoka-chan.

382
00:24:38,822 --> 00:24:41,232
Hey, good job. Thanks.

383
00:24:41,232 --> 00:24:44,942
Tell me about it. When Mikako Sensei's autograph session started,

384
00:24:44,942 --> 00:24:48,372
I was forced to be her manager. It was really tough.

385
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:51,852
Oh, you're Hinata Sensei, right?

386
00:24:51,852 --> 00:24:53,572
Yes.

387
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:59,952
Hi, it's been a while.

388
00:25:07,770 --> 00:25:09,388
Uncle.

389
00:25:12,070 --> 00:25:13,572
Looking for Kyoka-chan? She's over there.

390
00:25:13,572 --> 00:25:16,599
Here you go. Thank you very much.

391
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:20,742
How did the marriage meeting go?

392
00:25:20,742 --> 00:25:23,962
Well, it wasn't bad at all. We had a good conversation.

393
00:25:23,962 --> 00:25:25,822
- Really?
- Dad.

394
00:25:25,822 --> 00:25:28,812
- Hey.
- Buy something and contribute to our profits.

395
00:25:28,812 --> 00:25:31,525
So that's what it is, huh? Did you manage to sell our stuff?

396
00:25:31,525 --> 00:25:34,635
Yup. What's left are only these.

397
00:25:34,635 --> 00:25:38,285
Mom's scarf was sold rather quickly.

398
00:25:38,285 --> 00:25:40,552
- Scarf?
- Yeah.

399
00:25:40,552 --> 00:25:42,902
You know, the orange one.

400
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:45,552
No, I didn't throw that away.

401
00:25:45,552 --> 00:25:49,452
But it was in the box. Right, Hayate?

402
00:25:49,452 --> 00:25:51,462
- Did you check properly?
- I did.

403
00:25:51,462 --> 00:25:53,552
- But it was in the box.
- Why?

404
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:57,092
I'm so sorry! It's my fault.

405
00:25:57,092 --> 00:26:00,972
It was on top of the box this morning, so I just assumed.

406
00:26:00,972 --> 00:26:03,992
On top? It must have dropped!

407
00:26:03,992 --> 00:26:06,952
I'm truly sorry. It's all my fault.

408
00:26:06,952 --> 00:26:10,222
It's okay, Hayate. You didn't know that. There's nothing we can do.

409
00:26:10,222 --> 00:26:11,793
Sawada-san?

410
00:26:11,793 --> 00:26:13,552
Oh, Hinata-san.

411
00:26:13,552 --> 00:26:16,982
- What's happened?
- We made a mistake,

412
00:26:16,982 --> 00:26:19,792
and accidentally sold my mom's scarf during the bazaar.

413
00:26:19,792 --> 00:26:21,892
- Scarf?
- No need to worry.

414
00:26:21,892 --> 00:26:26,132
My wife would have wanted me to move on. Yup.

415
00:26:26,132 --> 00:26:29,422
You mean, the orange scarf that was here?

416
00:26:29,422 --> 00:26:32,662
- Yes.
- I remember the people who bought it.

417
00:26:32,662 --> 00:26:34,864
They were also at the yoga session just now.

418
00:26:34,864 --> 00:26:36,255
Really?

419
00:26:36,255 --> 00:26:39,615
They may still be around. What do they look like?

420
00:26:40,230 --> 00:26:41,912
It's two ladies in their 40s.

421
00:26:41,912 --> 00:26:44,242
They have bob hairstyles and were wearing yellow.

422
00:26:44,242 --> 00:26:46,792
They're the Tamagawa sisters.

423
00:26:46,792 --> 00:26:48,342
What do you mean?

424
00:26:48,342 --> 00:26:51,482
Don't you know them? I took a picture with them earlier.

425
00:26:51,482 --> 00:26:53,312
They're quite well-known in this area.

426
00:26:53,312 --> 00:26:55,932
I heard if you put it on your standby screen, you'll achieve happiness.

427
00:26:55,932 --> 00:26:59,352
It's now the buzz among high school girls in the Nikotama neighborhood.

428
00:26:59,352 --> 00:27:01,642
Now that you mention, after the yoga...

429
00:27:01,642 --> 00:27:05,882
<i>This marks the end of our session. Thank you very much.</i>

430
00:27:07,370 --> 00:27:10,452
<i>It feels so good. I worked out a sweat.</i>

431
00:27:10,452 --> 00:27:14,752
<i>Me too. Maybe I should head to the salon for a head spa after this?</i>

432
00:27:14,752 --> 00:27:17,052
<i>Great idea!</i>

433
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:20,122
<i>- All right if I join you?
- Of course.</i>

434
00:27:20,122 --> 00:27:23,222
<i>Sustainable, indeed!</i>

435
00:27:23,222 --> 00:27:24,492
Let's look for them.

436
00:27:24,492 --> 00:27:27,632
- They're probably at one of the salons around here.
- But...

437
00:27:27,632 --> 00:27:29,232
The scarf is important to you, right?

438
00:27:29,232 --> 00:27:31,072
Hurry!

439
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:35,532
- Yes, Ma'am!
- I'm going too.

440
00:27:35,532 --> 00:27:37,422
I'm counting on you!

441
00:27:46,830 --> 00:27:51,638
Bob hairstyle, yellow clothes.

442
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,340
You're the Tamagawa Sistersー

443
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:58,982
Not. Sorry about that.

444
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,959
Thank you very much.

445
00:28:12,959 --> 00:28:14,879
Let's go to the next one.

446
00:28:14,879 --> 00:28:18,439
The ladies have bob hairstyles and wear yellow clothes.

447
00:28:18,439 --> 00:28:21,549
- Understood. Thank you very much.
- No problem.

448
00:28:25,090 --> 00:28:27,240
Let's go to this salon next.

449
00:28:27,730 --> 00:28:29,490
It's enough.

450
00:28:30,170 --> 00:28:31,621
Huh?

451
00:28:31,621 --> 00:28:33,879
Really, it's enough.

452
00:28:35,150 --> 00:28:40,409
But... isn't it something important to you?

453
00:28:41,610 --> 00:28:45,749
My dream was to become a dictionary maker.

454
00:28:47,630 --> 00:28:54,219
But a dictionary only gets published once every seven, or eight years.

455
00:28:54,219 --> 00:29:00,249
Naturally, the number of scholars involved in compiling dictionaries is few and far between.

456
00:29:00,249 --> 00:29:02,229
I see.

457
00:29:02,229 --> 00:29:05,309
I didn't have much luck,

458
00:29:05,309 --> 00:29:09,289
and I wasn't selected for the editorial committee at that time.

459
00:29:18,130 --> 00:29:20,549
<i>What a pity.</i>

460
00:29:23,030 --> 00:29:26,470
<i>Rather than feeling it a pity,</i>

461
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:30,179
<i>I feel more frustrated than anything.</i>

462
00:29:30,179 --> 00:29:33,879
<i>Then, it's frustrating, right?</i>

463
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:39,149
<i>And sad, too. Perhaps.</i>

464
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:46,648
<i>Disappointed, heartbroken, dismayed,</i>

465
00:29:46,648 --> 00:29:52,769
<i>dejected, discouraged, miserable.</i>

466
00:29:52,769 --> 00:29:55,519
<i>Even though you know so many words</i>

467
00:29:55,519 --> 00:29:58,299
<i>associated with depressed emotions.</i>

468
00:29:59,970 --> 00:30:02,389
<i>I still feel frustrated, after all.</i>

469
00:30:04,610 --> 00:30:07,140
<i>So frustrating!</i>

470
00:30:23,620 --> 00:30:26,209
<i>I'm pathetic, right?</i>

471
00:30:26,209 --> 00:30:27,639
<i>Sorry.</i>

472
00:30:27,639 --> 00:30:30,009
<i>Seeing this side of you</i>

473
00:30:30,009 --> 00:30:32,609
<i>is my special privilege as your wife.</i>

474
00:30:47,540 --> 00:30:51,129
<i>I'm... so pathetic.</i>

475
00:31:02,180 --> 00:31:06,249
Let's go. We'll definitely find the scarf.

476
00:31:06,249 --> 00:31:07,596
Huh?

477
00:31:15,100 --> 00:31:17,210
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

478
00:31:17,210 --> 00:31:19,025
