- That's the one!
- What's this about?

499
00:32:37,260 --> 00:32:38,655
Sorry.

500
00:32:38,655 --> 00:32:41,845
But could you return that to us?

501
00:32:41,845 --> 00:32:44,475
Does this belong to a big brand, or something?

502
00:32:44,475 --> 00:32:50,675
No, but it's something very important to us.

503
00:32:50,675 --> 00:32:52,765
So, please.

504
00:32:54,620 --> 00:32:56,615
Please.

505
00:32:57,570 --> 00:33:00,522
Feels good.

506
00:33:00,522 --> 00:33:04,435
<i>Sustainable, indeed.</i>

507
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:09,435
So sorry to trouble you.

508
00:33:09,435 --> 00:33:11,599
You went out of your way to do this for me.

509
00:33:11,599 --> 00:33:14,826
No problem. I'm glad we found it.

510
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:19,005
I thought I'll be fine even without my wife's belongings.

511
00:33:19,005 --> 00:33:21,935
But I guess I couldn't let go.

512
00:33:21,935 --> 00:33:23,465
Yes.

513
00:33:24,090 --> 00:33:27,015
It's about time that I should move on.

514
00:33:27,015 --> 00:33:31,835
In fact, even now, I keep reminding myself about that every day.

515
00:33:31,835 --> 00:33:35,495
But it's only this one...

516
00:33:35,495 --> 00:33:37,635
I'm so pathetic.

517
00:33:39,460 --> 00:33:42,645
It's all right to be pathetic, isn't it?

518
00:33:43,710 --> 00:33:46,615
Your wife whom you hold dearly in your heart

519
00:33:46,615 --> 00:33:49,395
has also saved me.

520
00:33:50,780 --> 00:33:54,605
Did you see my snot on that scarf?

521
00:33:54,605 --> 00:33:56,115
What?

522
00:34:02,940 --> 00:34:06,599
It's tiring to just keep moving on.

523
00:34:07,650 --> 00:34:10,315
Don't close off these painful feelings.

524
00:34:10,315 --> 00:34:13,875
Just feel them, let them out,

525
00:34:13,875 --> 00:34:16,662
and accept them.

526
00:34:16,662 --> 00:34:19,902
That was what Kyoka-san said during her lesson just now.

527
00:34:23,570 --> 00:34:26,225
Now that we are older,

528
00:34:26,225 --> 00:34:28,733
we've gained lots of memories.

529
00:34:28,733 --> 00:34:31,405
We all carry them with us,

530
00:34:31,405 --> 00:34:35,565
but we'll look back on them occasionally as we walk on.

531
00:34:36,740 --> 00:34:39,535
Wouldn't that be enough?

532
00:34:55,030 --> 00:34:57,488
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

533
00:34:57,488 --> 00:35:00,558
- I'm dead tired.
- It's been a long day.

534
00:35:00,558 --> 00:35:02,701
You must be tired too, right, Hayate?

535
00:35:02,701 --> 00:35:04,972
Thanks for everything.

536
00:35:04,972 --> 00:35:07,725
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

537
00:35:07,725 --> 00:35:11,958
Uncle is already feeling sorry about it. So don't quarrel with him, all right?

538
00:35:11,958 --> 00:35:14,688
- I get it already.
- Really?

539
00:35:15,270 --> 00:35:16,826
Hey, you're back.

540
00:35:16,826 --> 00:35:18,008
I'm home.

541
00:35:18,008 --> 00:35:20,798
I'll go for my bath, then.

542
00:35:23,390 --> 00:35:25,728
Sorry about today.

543
00:35:25,728 --> 00:35:27,458
It's okay.

544
00:35:27,458 --> 00:35:31,038
Sorry. I didn't consider your feelings at all.

545
00:35:31,038 --> 00:35:35,508
No. Everything is fine already.

546
00:35:36,370 --> 00:35:41,105
In fact, people may not want to forget,

547
00:35:41,770 --> 00:35:45,608
but they'll start to forget gradually.

548
00:35:47,770 --> 00:35:50,510
There are times when I feel like seeing her.

549
00:35:50,510 --> 00:35:54,388
And I'll wonder if she'll suddenly appear from there.

550
00:35:58,620 --> 00:36:00,898
"Rintaro,

551
00:36:00,898 --> 00:36:04,853
please keep the mess to your own room only".

552
00:36:04,853 --> 00:36:07,468
Mom will say something like that, right?

553
00:36:10,790 --> 00:36:14,548
Your mom's voice sounds more refreshing than that.

554
00:36:14,548 --> 00:36:16,778
Hey, you're trying to beautify mom, aren't you?

555
00:36:16,778 --> 00:36:19,448
No, I'm not. Could it be your articulation?

556
00:36:19,448 --> 00:36:21,338
There's nothing wrong with my articulation.

557
00:36:21,338 --> 00:36:23,688
- Maybe it's how you end your words.
- How I end my words?

558
00:36:23,688 --> 00:36:25,868
Say "wakata kakage."

559
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:28,720
- "Wataka katage."
- "Wakata kakage."

560
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:30,824
- "Wataka takage."
- Not "wata".

561
00:36:30,824 --> 00:36:32,080
"Wataka takage."

562
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:34,370
Say it again.

563
00:36:34,370 --> 00:36:37,170
I said it right.

564
00:36:43,150 --> 00:36:46,268
Jeez, again! My phone, my phone...

565
00:36:46,268 --> 00:36:48,638
- Where is it?
- Here.

566
00:36:48,638 --> 00:36:51,245
Ah, thanks a bunch!

567
00:36:51,245 --> 00:36:54,355
You'll be back early today, so I'll cook dinner and wait for you.

568
00:36:54,355 --> 00:36:55,201
What?

569
00:36:55,201 --> 00:36:57,801
Your seminar has ended, right?

570
00:36:57,801 --> 00:37:00,185
Oh, yeah.

571
00:37:00,185 --> 00:37:03,148
- See you later.
- Be careful.

572
00:37:05,650 --> 00:37:07,258
She's left already?

573
00:37:07,258 --> 00:37:09,138
Uncle, you're going out?

574
00:37:09,138 --> 00:37:11,558
Yeah, I'm going out for a bit.

575
00:37:11,558 --> 00:37:13,938
- Be careful on your way.
- See you.

576
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:26,548
I'm sorry, but regarding the marriage meeting the other day, I wish to turn it down.

577
00:37:27,180 --> 00:37:29,871
Understood. Let me find another suitable person-

578
00:37:29,871 --> 00:37:34,141
Sorry. I'm not meeting anyone for the time being.

579
00:37:36,060 --> 00:37:39,048
I wish to cherish the time now

580
00:37:39,048 --> 00:37:41,938
when I can still meet the person I want to meet.

581
00:37:42,690 --> 00:37:44,465
The person you want to meet?

582
00:37:44,465 --> 00:37:49,215
There'll be times when I won't get my wish, but...

583
00:37:49,850 --> 00:37:53,498
even then, I want to feel that I can meet her.

584
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:02,906
That feeling of yours,

585
00:38:04,050 --> 00:38:08,104
I can totally understand.

586
00:38:09,330 --> 00:38:11,013
Really?

587
00:38:15,070 --> 00:38:17,728
Then, in that case...

588
00:38:17,728 --> 00:38:20,381
I'll erase this. Okay.

589
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:22,628
Thank you very much.

590
00:38:22,628 --> 00:38:24,771
Thank you.

591
00:38:24,771 --> 00:38:27,669
- See you next week.
- Thank you.

592
00:38:37,670 --> 00:38:40,428
- Hey there.
- Hello.

593
00:38:40,428 --> 00:38:43,788
Live in the moment.

594
00:38:46,780 --> 00:38:49,168
Do you feel alive right now?

595
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:29,198
<i>I thought it'd be nice to just hop on the first bus wherever.</i>

596
00:39:29,198 --> 00:39:33,073
<i>If the sand is above 29.5 degrees Celsius, the baby is a female.</i>

597
00:39:33,073 --> 00:39:36,603
<i>Anything below becomes a male.</i>

598
00:39:55,530 --> 00:39:57,678
Seita-san?

599
00:39:58,680 --> 00:40:00,628
Huh? Why?!

600
00:40:00,628 --> 00:40:04,154
"Why"? What about you?

601
00:40:04,154 --> 00:40:06,607
Oh, I was thinking today's the day of the seminar, so...

602
00:40:06,607 --> 00:40:10,777
You thought today's the day of the seminar, so you came here?

603
00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:15,328
Isn't it the same for you?

604
00:40:16,200 --> 00:40:17,978
No, it's not.

605
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:43,164
- He turned it down?
- Yes.

606
00:40:43,164 --> 00:40:45,178
My dad...

607
00:40:47,030 --> 00:40:50,428
still can't forget my mom, after all.

608
00:40:51,110 --> 00:40:54,718
But Mr. Sawada looked happy.

609
00:40:54,718 --> 00:40:56,863
- Is that so?
- Yes.

610
00:40:59,310 --> 00:41:01,729
When my mom died,

611
00:41:01,729 --> 00:41:06,639
my dad wouldn't eat anything.

612
00:41:07,350 --> 00:41:12,768
But even so, he'd still water the houseplants that my mom left behind.

613
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:15,468
He seemed to take it real hard.

614
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:21,008
At that time, how did you handle it?

615
00:41:21,008 --> 00:41:22,648
Me?

616
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:25,828
What I did was...

617
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:49,808
<i>Dad, what do you want to eat for dinner?</i>

618
00:41:49,808 --> 00:41:53,178
<i>Fried pork with ginger? It's your favorite, right?</i>

619
00:41:59,438 --> 00:42:01,582
<i>[Preparation for Cherry Blossom-Viewing!]</i>

620
00:42:01,582 --> 00:42:03,434
<i>Mom...</i>

621
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:37,157
<i>What do you think?</i>

622
00:42:37,980 --> 00:42:39,326
<i>Yeah.</i>

623
00:42:41,690 --> 00:42:43,314
<i>Looks good.</i>

624
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:47,998
<i>It's good.</i>

625
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:59,201
I was desperately...

626
00:42:59,201 --> 00:43:02,811
<i>trying to make my dad human again.</i>

627
00:43:05,210 --> 00:43:06,868
And also,

628
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:10,418
I had to settle all the funeral procedures.

629
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:14,688
When a person dies,

630
00:43:15,870 --> 00:43:20,528
there are many things you have to settle until you're so fed up.

631
00:43:22,150 --> 00:43:24,905
If I had broken down too,

632
00:43:24,905 --> 00:43:28,625
my home would have turned into a rubbish dump.

633
00:43:31,030 --> 00:43:35,778
But... you must be hurting too, weren't you?

634
00:43:37,670 --> 00:43:39,620
I...

635
00:43:43,430 --> 00:43:45,649
My dad was hurting...

636
00:43:45,649 --> 00:43:48,018
more than me...

637
00:43:54,460 --> 00:43:56,038
Huh?

638
00:44:01,150 --> 00:44:03,058
Why am I crying?

639
00:44:04,390 --> 00:44:06,748
It's a natural response.

640
00:44:06,748 --> 00:44:09,378
After all, your mom passed away.

641
00:44:37,330 --> 00:44:39,298
I miss her.

642
00:44:41,930 --> 00:44:46,308
I want to see her. Just once.

643
00:45:02,640 --> 00:45:09,800
♫ <i>I walk alone on my way back home</i> ♫

644
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:13,200
♫ <i>The song coming from my headphones</i> ♫

645
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:15,300
Seita-san.

646
00:45:16,213 --> 00:45:17,840
Yes?

647
00:45:18,688 --> 00:45:21,538
At this rate...

648
00:45:21,538 --> 00:45:26,830
♫ <i>You taught me about small fortunes</i> ♫

649
00:45:28,210 --> 00:45:31,928
I'll become an old lady who does nothing but complain.

650
00:45:33,280 --> 00:45:35,070
Huh?

651
00:45:35,070 --> 00:45:39,250
♫ <i>Showing you from behind</i> ♫

652
00:45:39,250 --> 00:45:41,890
♫ <i>Who knows how long</i> ♫

653
00:45:41,890 --> 00:45:43,830
I miss her.

654
00:45:45,158 --> 00:45:49,780
♫ <i>I already have only you in my eyes</i> ♫

655
00:45:49,780 --> 00:45:51,810
Even in the future,

656
00:45:52,363 --> 00:45:54,490
I want to see her.

657
00:45:56,540 --> 00:46:03,200
♫ <i>I bring it into focus</i> ♫

658
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:07,960
♫ <i>Even your slovenly swaying back</i> ♫

